A vintage 1990s-style illustration of a well-organized wooden filing cabinet with multiple drawers partially open, revealing neatly arranged colorful folders and documents. Beside it, an old beige desktop computer monitor displays a simple folder tree structure. Scattered around the scene are small moving boxes with arrows pointing to different shelves and compartments, suggesting reorganization and migration. The warm, muted color palette features mustard yellows, burnt oranges, and olive greens typical of late 20th century office aesthetics. Dust motes float in a beam of light from a nearby window with venetian blinds, casting striped shadows across the scene. The composition emphasizes order emerging from potential chaos, with some folders mid-transition between locations, capturing the essence of thoughtful digital housekeeping and systematic upgrades.
